: nums = [-2,-1,-1,1,2,3]\nOutput: 3\nExplanation: There are 3 positive integers and 3 negative integers. The maximum count among them is 3.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: nums = [-3,-2,-1,0,0,1,2]\nOutput: 3\nExplanation: There are 2 positive integers and 3 negative integers. The maximum count among them is 3.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: nums = [5,20,66,1314]\nOutput: 4\nExplanation: There are 4 positive integers and 0 negative integers. The maximum count among them is 4.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 2000`\n\n- `-2000 <= nums[i] <= 2000`\n\n- `nums` is sorted in a **non-decreasing order**.\n\n**Follow up:** Can you solve the problem in `O(log(n))` time complexity?","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-count-of-positive-integer-and-negative-integer/","problemName":"Maximum Count of Positive Integer and Negative Integer","problemNumber":2529,"problemSlug":"maximum-count-of-positive-integer-and-negative-integer","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":2529,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Array","Greedy","Heap (Priority Queue)"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given a **0-indexed** integer array `nums` and an integer `k`. You have a **starting score** of `0`.\n\nIn one **operation**:\n\n- choose an index `i` such that `0 <= i < nums.length`,\n\n- increase your **score** by `nums[i]`, and\n\n- replace `nums[i]` with `ceil(nums[i] / 3)`.\n\nReturn *the maximum possible **score** you can attain after applying **exactly*** `k` *operations*.\n\nThe ceiling function `ceil(val)` is the least integer greater than or equal to `val`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: nums = [10,10,10,10,10], k = 5\nOutput: 50\nExplanation: Apply the operation to each array element exactly once. The final score is 10 + 10 + 10 + 10 + 10 = 50.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums = [1,10,3,3,3], k = 3\nOutput: 17\nExplanati