al number of gifts remaining is 29.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: gifts = [1,1,1,1], k = 4\nOutput: 4\nExplanation: \nIn this case, regardless which pile you choose, you have to leave behind 1 gift in each pile. \nThat is, you can't take any pile with you. \nSo, the total gifts remaining are 4.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= gifts.length <= 10³`\n\n- `1 <= gifts[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- `1 <= k <= 10³`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/take-gifts-from-the-richest-pile/","problemName":"Take Gifts From the Richest Pile","problemNumber":2558,"problemSlug":"take-gifts-from-the-richest-pile","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":2558,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Array","String","Prefix Sum"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given a **0-indexed** array of strings `words` and a 2D array of integers `queries`.\n\nEach query `queries[i] = [li, ri]` asks us to find the number of strings present at the indices ranging from `li` to `ri` (both **inclusive**) of `words` that start and end with a vowel.\n\nReturn *an array *`ans`* of size *`queries.length`*, where *`ans[i]`* is the answer to the *`i`^(th)* query*.\n\n**Note** that the vowel letters are `'a'`, `'e'`, `'i'`, `'o'`, and `'u'`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: words = [\"aba\",\"bcb\",\"ece\",\"aa\",\"e\"], queries = [[0,2],[1,4],[1,1]]\nOutput: [2,3,0]\nExplanation: The strings starting and ending with a vowel are \"aba\", \"ece\", \"aa\" and \"e\".\nThe answer to the query [0,2] is 2 (strings \"aba\" and \"ece\").\nto query [1,4] is 3 (strings \"ece\", \"aa\", \"e\").\nto query [1,1] is 0.\nWe return [2,3,0].","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: words = [\"a\",\"e\",\"i\"], queries = [[0,2],[0,1],[2,2]]\nOutput: [3,2,1]\nExplanation: Every string satisfies the conditions, so we return [3,2,1].","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= words.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= words[i].length <= 40`\n\n- `words[i]` consists only of lowercase English letters.\n\n- `sum(words[i].length) <= 3 * 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= queries.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `0 <= li <= ri < words.length`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","String","Prefix Sum"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given a **0-indexed** array of strings `words` and a 2D array of integers `queries`.\n\nEach query `queries[i] = [li, ri]` asks us to find the number of strings present at the indices ranging from `li` to `ri` (both **inclusive**) of `words` that start and end with a vowel.\n\nReturn *an array *`ans`* of size *`queries.length`*, where *`ans[i]`* is the answer to the *`i`^(th)* query*.\n\n**Note** that the vowel letters are `'a'`, `'e'`, `'i'`, `'o'`, and `'u'`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: words = [\"aba\",\"bcb\",\"ece\",\"aa\",\"e\"], queries = [[0,2],[1,4],[1,1]]\nOutput: [2,3,0]\nExplanation: The strings starting and ending with a vowel are \"aba\", \"ece\", \"aa\" and \"e\".\nThe answer to the query [0,2] is 2 (strings \"aba\" and \"ece\").\nto query [1,4] is 3 (strings \"ece\", \"aa\", \"e\").\nto query [1,1] is 0.\nWe return [2,3,0].\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: words = [\"a\",\"e\",\"i\"], queries = [[0,2],[0,1],[2,2]]\nOutput: [3,2,1]\nExplanation: Every string satisfies the conditions, so we return [3,2,1].\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= words.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= words[i].length <= 40`\n\n- `words[i]` consists only of lowercase English letters.\n\n- `sum(words[i].length) <= 3 * 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= queries.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `0 <= li <= ri < words.length`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/count-vowel-strings-in-ranges/","problemName":"Count Vowel Strings in Ranges","problemNumber":2559,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":