um and minimum values Bob can make by remapping **exactly** **one** digit in *`num`.\n\n**Notes:**\n\n- When Bob remaps a digit d1 to another digit d2, Bob replaces all occurrences of `d1` in `num` with `d2`.\n\n- Bob can remap a digit to itself, in which case `num` does not change.\n\n- Bob can remap different digits for obtaining minimum and maximum values respectively.\n\n- The resulting number after remapping can contain leading zeroes.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: num = 11891\nOutput: 99009\nExplanation: \nTo achieve the maximum value, Bob can remap the digit 1 to the digit 9 to yield 99899.\nTo achieve the minimum value, Bob can remap the digit 1 to the digit 0, yielding 890.\nThe difference between these two numbers is 99009.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: num = 90\nOutput: 99\nExplanation:\nThe maximum value that can be returned by the function is 99 (if 0 is replaced by 9) and the minimum value that can be returned by the function is 0 (if 9 is replaced by 0).\nThus, we return 99.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= num <= 10⁸`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-difference-by-remapping-a-digit/","problemName":"Maximum Difference by Remapping a Digit","problemNumber":2566,"problemSlug":"maximum-difference-by-remapping-a-digit","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":2566,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Array","Greedy","Sorting"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given an integer array `nums`.\n\n- The **low** score of `nums` is the **minimum** absolute difference between any two integers.\n\n- The **high** score of `nums` is the **maximum** absolute difference between any two integers.\n\n- The **score** of `nums` is the sum of the **high** and **low** scores.\n\nReturn the **minimum score** after **changing two elements** of `nums`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n**Input:** nums = [1,4,7,8,5]\n\n**Output:** 3\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n- Change `nums[0]` and `nums[1]` to be 6 so that `nums` becomes [6,6,7,8,5].\