 *an array containing all the answers to the third type queries.*\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: nums1 = [1,0,1], nums2 = [0,0,0], queries = [[1,1,1],[2,1,0],[3,0,0]]\nOutput: [3]\nExplanation: After the first query nums1 becomes [1,1,1]. After the second query, nums2 becomes [1,1,1], so the answer to the third query is 3. Thus, [3] is returned.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums1 = [1], nums2 = [5], queries = [[2,0,0],[3,0,0]]\nOutput: [5]\nExplanation: After the first query, nums2 remains [5], so the answer to the second query is 5. Thus, [5] is returned.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums1.length,nums2.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `nums1.length = nums2.length`\n\n- `1 <= queries.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `queries[i].length = 3`\n\n- `0 <= l <= r <= nums1.length - 1`\n\n- `0 <= p <= 10⁶`\n\n- `0 <= nums1[i] <= 1`\n\n- `0 <= nums2[i] <= 10⁹`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Segment Tree"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Hard","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given two **0-indexed** arrays `nums1` and `nums2` and a 2D array `queries` of queries. There are three types of queries:\n\n- For a query of type 1, `queries[i] = [1, l, r]`. Flip the values from `0` to `1` and from `1` to `0` in `nums1` from index `l` to index `r`. Both `l` and `r` are **0-indexed**.\n\n- For a query of type 2, `queries[i] = [2, p, 0]`. For every index `0 <= i < n`, set `nums2[i] = nums2[i] + nums1[i] * p`.\n\n- For a query of type 3, `queries[i] = [3, 0, 0]`. Find the sum of the elements in `nums2`.\n\nReturn *an array containing all the answers to the third type queries.*\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: nums1 = [1,0,1], nums2 = [0,0,0], queries = [[1,1,1],[2,1,0],[3,0,0]]\nOutput: [3]\nExplanation: After the first query nums1 becomes [1,1,1]. After the second query, nums2 becomes [1,1,1], so the answer to the thi