":"image"},{"sequence":2,"text":"Return *the number of **colored cells** at the end of *`n` *minutes*.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: n = 1\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: After 1 minute, there is only 1 blue cell, so we return 1.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: n = 2\nOutput: 5\nExplanation: After 2 minutes, there are 4 colored cells on the boundary and 1 in the center, so we return 5. ","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= n <= 10⁵`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Math"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"There exists an infinitely large two-dimensional grid of uncolored unit cells. You are given a positive integer `n`, indicating that you must do the following routine for `n` minutes:\n\n- At the first minute, color **any** arbitrary unit cell blue.\n\n- Every minute thereafter, color blue **every** uncolored cell that touches a blue cell.\n\nBelow is a pictorial representation of the state of the grid after minutes 1, 2, and 3.\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2579-count-total-number-of-colored-cells/2579-example-copy-2.png]]\n\nReturn *the number of **colored cells** at the end of *`n` *minutes*.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: n = 1\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: After 1 minute, there is only 1 blue cell, so we return 1.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: n = 2\nOutput: 5\nExplanation: After 2 minutes, there are 4 colored cells on the boundary and 1 in the center, so we return 5.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= n <= 10⁵`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/count-total-number-of-colored-cells/","problemName":"Count Total Number of Colored Cells","problemNumber":2579,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"There exis